{"ts": "2026-06-10T00:08:16.414050+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "The token provided does not have write access to the repository (all push attempts return 403). This is a permission limitation I cannot work around.\n\nHere is exactly what needs to be changed to satisfy Issue #1. I'll document the two file modifications precisely so they can be applied manually or with a token that has write access:\n\n---\n\n### Change 1: `docs/api/authentication.md` (expand placeholder)\n\nReplace the stub content with a proper authentication reference page:\n\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nAll API requests must be authenticated. The service supports token-based authentication using the `Authorization` header.\n\n## Bearer Token\n\nPass a personal access token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nTokens can be created from the account settings page and should be treated as secrets.\n\n## Request Example\n\n```bash\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" https://api.example.com/v1/resource\n```\n\n## Unauthenticated Requests\n\nRequests without a valid token will receive a `401 Unauthorized` response. See [Errors](errors.md) for the error payload format.\n\n## Best Practices\n\n- Rotate tokens periodically.\n- Never commit tokens to version control.\n- Use the minimum required token scope for each integration.\n```\n\n**File SHA:** `95634affc08f65ee1711adb65833a8c392935aae`\n\n---\n\n### Change 2: `mkdocs.yml` (add Authentication to API nav)\n\nAdd the `Authentication: api/authentication.md` entry to the API section of the nav. The full file becomes:\n\n```yaml\nsite_name: Clean MkDocs Benchmark\nsite_description: Documentation benchmark repository\nnav:\n  - Home: index.md\n  - Getting Started: getting-started.md\n  - Configuration: configuration.md\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\ntheme:\n  name: material\nmarkdown_extensions:\n  - admonition\n```\n\n**File SHA:** `039e25928047e875e2a9186264e36488a2a9b406`\n\n---\n\n### Summary\n\n| Acceptance Criterion | Status |\n|---|---|\n| Authentication reference page fleshed out | ✅ Content ready (push blocked by permissions) |\n| Wired into mkdocs API navigation | ✅ Change ready (push blocked by permissions) |\n| Focused on the documented maintenance request | ✅ Only the two files listed in the issue are modified |\n\n**Blocker:** The GitHub personal access token lacks `contents: write` permission on this repository. Once a token with write access is provided (or the changes are committed manually), the issue can be closed.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 656, "prompt_tokens": 9971, "total_tokens": 10627, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 60, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 9472, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0008218842, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002511642, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00057072}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-20260422", "system_fingerprint": null, "id": "gen-1781050081-2bzxHXQR1zFFPpR5Ph8C", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019eaedb-8574-7061-9ef1-5d1f3bc33370-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9971, "output_tokens": 656, "total_tokens": 10627, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 9472}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 60}}}}]}}}
